{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gj6zZNtHvxDMLWt3WXWEbv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 9.2: Custom Workflow Creation\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want to create a custom workflow YAML in my project and run it via `codeharness run --workflow my-workflow`,\n11\tso that I can define non-standard execution flows without patching the embedded default.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a custom workflow file at `.codeharness/workflows/my-workflow.yaml` with valid `tasks` and `flow` sections\n16\t   **When** `codeharness run --workflow my-workflow` executes\n17\t   **Then** the custom workflow is loaded from `.codeharness/workflows/my-workflow.yaml`, validated against the workflow JSON schema, and used as the workflow for execution\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a custom workflow file at `.codeharness/workflows/my-workflow.yaml`\n21\t   **When** the file fails JSON schema validation (e.g., missing `tasks` key, unknown properties, invalid task fields)\n22\t   **Then** a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown with specific schema validation errors and the file path\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** a custom workflow file that passes schema validation but has dangling task references in `flow` (e.g., `flow: [nonexistent]` where `nonexistent` is not defined in `tasks`)\n26\t   **When** the workflow resolver loads and validates it\n27\t   **Then** a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown with referential integrity errors listing the dangling references\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** agent references in a custom workflow (e.g., `agent: my-custom-agent`)\n31\t   **When** the workflow is resolved and agents are compiled\n32\t   **Then** agent references resolve through the same embedded -> user -> project config chain as the default workflow\n33\t   **And** unknown agent names cause an error at agent resolution time (not at workflow parse time)\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t5. **Given** the `codeharness run` command\n37\t   **When** invoked with `--workflow my-workflow`\n38\t   **Then** `resolveWorkflow()` is called with `{ cwd: projectDir, name: 'my-workflow' }` instead of the default name\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t6. **Given** `--workflow my-workflow` is specified but no file exists at `.codeharness/workflows/my-workflow.yaml` and no embedded template exists for that name\n42\t   **When** `codeharness run --workflow my-workflow` executes\n43\t   **Then** the command exits with a clear error message indicating the workflow was not found\n44\t   **And** the error message includes the expected file path\n45\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n46\t\n47\t7. **Given** `codeharness run` is invoked without `--workflow`\n48\t   **When** the command executes\n49\t   **Then** the default workflow resolution chain (embedded -> user patch -> project patch) is used unchanged (backward-compatible)\n50\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n51\t\n52\t8. **Given** a custom workflow at `.codeharness/workflows/ci.yaml` alongside a patch at `.codeharness/workflows/ci.patch.yaml`\n53\t   **When** the workflow resolver loads `ci`\n54\t   **Then** the custom workflow is loaded directly (not patched) because it has no `extends` key — the patch file is ignored for full custom workflows\n55\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n56\t\n57\t9. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n58\t   **When** the build completes\n59\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero errors\n60\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n61\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n62\t\n63\t10. **Given** unit tests for custom workflow creation\n64\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n65\t    **Then** tests cover: custom workflow loading by name, schema validation of custom workflows, referential integrity of custom workflows, `--workflow` CLI flag plumbing, missing workflow error path, backward-compatible default behavior, agent resolution with custom agent names\n66\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n67\t\n68\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n69\t\n70\t- [x] Task 1: Add `--workflow` CLI option to `src/commands/run.ts` (AC: #5, #6, #7)\n71\t  - [x] Add `.option('--workflow <name>', 'Workflow name to load (default: \"default\")')` to the run command definition\n72\t  - [x] Pass `options.workflow ?? 'default'` as the `name` parameter to `resolveWorkflow({ cwd: projectDir, name: workflowName })`\n73\t  - [x] Keep the fallback logic for backward compatibility — if `resolveWorkflow` fails and name is `'default'`, try direct file parse\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 2: Verify `resolveWorkflow()` already handles custom workflows by name (AC: #1, #2, #3, #8)\n76\t  - [x] Confirm `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'my-workflow' })` loads `.codeharness/workflows/my-workflow.yaml` as a full custom workflow when no `extends` key is present (this path already exists at lines 312-319 of `workflow-parser.ts`)\n77\t  - [x] Confirm that if no custom file exists and no embedded template exists for that name, `resolveWorkflow` throws `WorkflowParseError` with \"Embedded workflow not found\" (this is the existing error at line 329)\n78\t  - [x] Confirm schema validation and referential integrity checks run on custom workflows (they go through `parseWorkflow` which calls `validateAndResolve`)\n79\t  - [x] If any of the above behaviors are missing or broken, fix them\n80\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XS4sVgQGUVdaHQcMbvghrp","session_id":"e499f49a-fe4c-4b28-bb21-4e83348f2671","uuid":"5203ccd4-9a94-43ec-bdbc-6d87a157cdbf","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:19:14.620Z"}
