{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XS4sVgQGUVdaHQcMbvghrp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-agentdriver-interface-types.md`.\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 10.1\n- Story Key: 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types\n- File: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-agentdriver-interface-types.md`\n- Status: ready-for-dev\n- Sprint-status.yaml: NOT modified (per instructions)\n\n**Summary:** Created story 10-1 with 11 acceptance criteria covering the full AgentDriver interface refactoring. All ACs are tagged `test-provable` because this is a pure types/interfaces story — everything can be verified by building and running tests without a running application.\n\n**What the story covers:**\n- New `AgentDriver` interface with `dispatch()` returning `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`\n- New types: `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `DispatchOpts`, `ErrorCategory`, `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus`\n- Backward-compatible deprecation of old types (`SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent`)\n- Extension of `ResultEvent` with optional `cost_usd` field\n- Updated barrel exports and unit tests\n\n**Next Steps:**\n1. Review the story file\n2. Run `dev-story` for implementation\n3. Run `code-review` when complete\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **No problems encountered.** The epic definition in `epics-multi-framework.md` was clear and mapped directly to the architecture document.\n- **Workaround: Epic numbering mismatch.** The sprint-status uses \"Epic 10\" numbering (10-1, 10-2...) but the epics file uses \"Epic 1\" internally (Story 1.1, 1.2...). I mapped 10-1 to Epic 1 Story 1.1 in the multi-framework epics. This is expected — the sprint tracker renumbers epics globally.\n- **Risk: `OutputContract` type placement.** The architecture places `output-contract.ts` as a separate module, but the type needs to be in `types.ts` because `DispatchOpts` references it. The dev agent must put the TYPE in `types.ts` and the IMPLEMENTATION (serialize/deserialize) in a later story's separate module. This is called out in the Dev Notes.\n- **Observation:** The existing `AgentDriver` interface is very different from the target (process-based vs async-iterable-based). The deprecated type preservation is important because `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` has 288 lines of tests against the old interface shape.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines), `wc -l` (~1 line)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none — each read/glob served a distinct purpose"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2658a775cfd48181 (use SendMessage with to: 'a2658a775cfd48181' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 62640\ntool_uses: 29\nduration_ms: 158863</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e499f49a-fe4c-4b28-bb21-4e83348f2671","uuid":"2b524776-c8b4-4a4b-9865-b2cc1b317ca7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:21:09.471Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-create-story for story 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed. Examples: 'function X exists', 'type Y is exported', 'test Z passes', 'file has <300 lines'.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior (CLI output, HTTP response, process lifecycle). No Docker stack needed. Examples: 'CLI prints usage when invoked with --help', 'server responds 200 on /health', 'process exits 0 on valid input'.\n- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service interaction). Examples: 'logs appear in VictoriaLogs', 'metrics are emitted to VictoriaMetrics', 'container communicates with service X'.\n- `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment). This is rare. Examples: 'UI looks correct on mobile', 'payment processes successfully in production'.\n\nDefault to `test-provable` when unsure. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"a2658a775cfd48181","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-agentdriver-interface-types.md`.\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 10.1\n- Story Key: 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types\n- File: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-agentdriver-interface