{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BpPAVp4Nca1DbqKcGEGyds","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All clean.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types\n**Files reviewed:** `src/lib/agents/types.ts`, `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts`, `src/lib/agents/index.ts`, `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`\n\n### Issues Found & Fixed (HIGH + MEDIUM)\n\n| # | Severity | Issue | Fix |\n|---|----------|-------|-----|\n| 1 | HIGH | `DispatchOpts` fields mutable — drivers could mutate caller's options | Added `readonly` to all fields, `readonly string[]` for arrays |\n| 2 | MEDIUM | `DriverCapabilities` fields mutable — consumers could flip driver flags | Added `readonly` to all 3 boolean fields |\n| 3 | MEDIUM | `DriverHealth` fields mutable | Added `readonly` to all 4 fields |\n| 4 | MEDIUM | `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus` fields mutable — contract data should be immutable | Added `readonly` throughout, `readonly string[]` and `readonly ACStatus[]` for arrays |\n| 5 | MEDIUM | Test name \"covers all 8 event types\" but array has 9 entries and assertion checks 9 | Fixed name to \"covers all 9 event variants\" |\n| 6 | MEDIUM | `ErrorCategory` exhaustiveness test is weak — just checks array length | Added compile-time exhaustiveness test with `never` default in switch |\n\n### Coverage Results\n\n- Overall: **96.75%** (target: 90%) -- PASS\n- Per-file floor: **all 163 files above 80%** -- PASS\n- Tests: **33 passing** in types.test.ts (was 32, +1 exhaustiveness test)\n\n### Story Status\n\nUpdated from `review` to `verifying`.\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `DispatchOpts` allowed mutation of dispatch options by drivers, violating the architecture's stateless driver contract\n- MEDIUM (x4): Mutable interface fields on `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus` — inconsistent with `readonly` convention used in `StreamEvent` types\n- MEDIUM: Test name/count mismatch (\"8 event types\" vs 9 actual)\n- MEDIUM: `ErrorCategory` exhaustiveness test was cosmetic (array length only), not compile-time safe\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `ACStatus.status` is typed as `string` rather than a union type (e.g., `'passed' | 'failed' | 'skipped'`). This allows arbitrary strings. The architecture doc doesn't constrain it, so leaving as tech debt for a future story.\n- `SpawnOpts` deprecated type still uses mutable fields. Not worth fixing since it's scheduled for removal in story 10-3.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. All files above per-file floor, overall above target.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The architecture spec (Decision 1) does NOT include `readonly capabilities: DriverCapabilities` on the `AgentDriver` interface, but the story AC #1 explicitly requires it. The story was followed. This is a spec drift that should be reconciled — either update the architecture doc or acknowledge the story extended the spec intentionally.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story moved to `verifying`.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 8, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run build` (~18 lines), `git diff HEAD -- src/lib/agents/index.ts` (~30 lines), `codeharness coverage` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: `npm run build` ran twice (once for initial verification, once after fixes — both necessary). No other redundancy."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a574ad89103ae5832 (use SendMessage with to: 'a574ad89103ae5832' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 50474\ntool_uses: 37\nduration_ms: 201194</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e499f49a-fe4c-4b28-bb21-4e83348f2671","uuid":"e4d4e934-f843-4240-9b32-1cedcf0dd0bf","timestamp":"2026-04