{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PsiQhzBk4aJjbG1zxVw97Y","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e499f49a-fe4c-4b28-bb21-4e83348f2671","uuid":"7502bd65-f246-45f4-9835-85b923d4a35d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:30:44.138Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Redundant operations: none significant","newString":"- Redundant operations: none significant\n\n### 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types — code-review (2026-04-03T06:30)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** `DispatchOpts` fields mutable — drivers could mutate caller's options. Added `readonly`.\n- **MEDIUM fixed (x4):** Mutable fields on `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus`.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Test name/count mismatch (\"8 event types\" vs 9 actual).\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** `ErrorCategory` exhaustiveness test was cosmetic, not compile-time safe. Added `never` switch.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `ACStatus.status` is typed as `string` rather than a union type.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `SpawnOpts` deprecated type still uses mutable fields (scheduled for removal in 10-3).\n- **Architecture concern:** Story AC #1 added `capabilities` to `AgentDriver` interface, which isn't in the architecture spec (Decision 1). Spec drift.\n- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 8, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `git diff` (~30 lines), `npm run build` (~18 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: `npm run build` ran twice (both necessary)","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 3)\n\n### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — create-story (2026-04-03T02:42)\n\n- **Risk — `replace` semantics new:** AC #2 introduces `replace` (full section overwrite) not present in agent-resolver.ts. Must apply AFTER `overrides` to avoid clobbering.\n- **Schema `additionalProperties: false`:** workflow.schema.json blocks patch validation. Patch files can't be validated against same schema.\n- **`deepMerge` not shared:** Function in agent-resolver.ts needs extraction to shared util or duplication = tech debt.\n- All 10 ACs test-provable.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 13\n- By tool: Read: 6, Glob: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — dev-story (2026-04-03T02:47)\n\n- **Real filesystem usage in test:** User-level patch ordering test writes/restores `~/.codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml` on real filesystem. Crash mid-test could leave stale file. Acceptable tech debt.\n- **`deepMerge` duplication:** Duplicated between agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts. Should be extracted to shared utility in future story.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 7, Edit: 13, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~800 lines), `npm run test:unit` (~600 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: one file read twice (workflow-parser.test.ts)\n\n### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — code-review (2026-04-03T02:55)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** ~75 lines duplicated validation/integrity/defaults between `parseWorkflow()` and `resolveWorkflow()`. Extracted `validateAndResolve()`.\n- **HIGH fixed:** `loadWorkflowPatch` silently swallowed EACCES permission errors. Now throws on permission errors, null only for missing files.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Empty catch clause in embedded workflow loading discarded original error message.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** No test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'custom' })` path. Added.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `deepMerge` duplicated in agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Custom workflow detection re-reads file that `parseWorkflow` also reads (minor I/O waste).\n- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — verification (2026-04-03T02:58)\n\n- **Proof format mismatch:** First proof used `### AC N:` (h3) instead of `## AC N:` (h2) and lacked bash/output block pairs. Rewrote.\n- **Warnings:** Showboat not installed, no exec-plan — non-blocking.\n- **BATS integration tests:** All show exit code 127 (pre-existing, unrelated).\n- **Branch coverage 79.12%:** Below 80% for branches specifically, but AC says \"80%+ coverage\" without specifying branches. Statement 93.96%, functions 100%.\n- All 10/10 ACs passed with real evidence.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test | tail -80` (~80 lines), `vitest run workflow-parser.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (~45 lines)\n- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n- Redundant operations: vitest coverage run twice, npm run test:unit run twice\n\n### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — create-story (2026-04-03T07:06)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** The epic's ACs for story 9.2 are sparse (3 lines). Expanded to 10 ACs covering error paths, backward compatibility, edge cases (custom + patch coexistence), and agent resolution.\n- **Story is smaller than expected:** Most heavy lifting done in story 9-1. resolveWorkflow() already accepts a `name` parameter and detects full custom workflows. This story is primarily CLI plumbing + test coverage.\n- **Risk — user-level custom workflows unsupported:** resolveWorkflow() only checks project-level for full custom workflows. User-level custom workflows are only supported as patches, not full workflows.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 6, Edit: 0, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 5\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Two separate Glob calls for same pattern — minor\n\n### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — dev-story (2026-04-03T07:10)\n\nNo issues reported. Clean implementation — existing resolveWorkflow() already supported the name parameter.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Glob: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — code-review (2026-04-03T07:15)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Path traversal vulnerability via `--workflow` CLI flag — no input sanitization allowed `../` sequences to escape `.codeharness/workflows/` directory. Fixed with regex validation.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Wrong error variable in `run.ts` fallback catch block (`err` → `fallbackErr`).\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Test assertions strengthened for `cwd` and error message content.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicate test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'nonexistent' })` between 9.2 section and pre-existing test.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Legacy fallback path in run.ts should eventually be removed.\n- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff` (~200 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — verification (2026-04-03T07:20)\n\n- **Proof format issues:** Initial proof had 8/10 ACs because ACs 9-10 lacked bash+output paired code blocks. Fixed.\n- **Tier header mismatch:** Proof used `**Verification tier:**` instead of `**Tier:**` — validator regex only matches latter. Fixed.\n- **Observation:** Vitest ANSI escape codes make grep-based extraction unreliable from raw output.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 4, Grep: 8, Edit: 3, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~600 lines ANSI), `npm run test:unit -- --coverage` (~100 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Coverage and test:unit run separately (could be one), verify run 3 times due to proof format fixes\n\n### 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types — create-story (2026-04-03T06:20)\n\n- **Workaround: Epic numbering mismatch.** Sprint-status uses \"Epic 10\" (10-1, 10-2...) but epics file uses \"Epic 1\" internally (Story 1.1, 1.2...). Mapped 10-1 to Epic 1 Story 1.1 in the multi-framework epics.\n- **Risk: `OutputContract` type placement.** Architecture places `output-contract.ts` as a separate module, but the type needs to be in `types.ts` because `DispatchOpts` references it. TYPE in `types.ts`, IMPLEMENTATION in later story.\n- **Observation:** Existing `AgentDriver` interface is very different from target (process-based vs async-iterable-based). Deprecated type preservation important — 288 lines of tests against old interface.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types — dev-story (2026-04-03T06:25)\n\nNo issues reported. Clean implementation — 4 files modified, 30+ tests, all 4219 tests passing.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 13, Grep: 3, Write: 3, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~40 lines), `npx tsc --noEmit` (