{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SH5t4mRnzGr7m63kkGpqSU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 3)\n2\t\n3\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — create-story (2026-04-03T02:42)\n4\t\n5\t- **Risk — `replace` semantics new:** AC #2 introduces `replace` (full section overwrite) not present in agent-resolver.ts. Must apply AFTER `overrides` to avoid clobbering.\n6\t- **Schema `additionalProperties: false`:** workflow.schema.json blocks patch validation. Patch files can't be validated against same schema.\n7\t- **`deepMerge` not shared:** Function in agent-resolver.ts needs extraction to shared util or duplication = tech debt.\n8\t- All 10 ACs test-provable.\n9\t\n10\t## Token Report — create-story\n11\t- Total tool calls: 13\n12\t- By tool: Read: 6, Glob: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n13\t- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n14\t- Redundant operations: none\n15\t\n16\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — dev-story (2026-04-03T02:47)\n17\t\n18\t- **Real filesystem usage in test:** User-level patch ordering test writes/restores `~/.codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml` on real filesystem. Crash mid-test could leave stale file. Acceptable tech debt.\n19\t- **`deepMerge` duplication:** Duplicated between agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts. Should be extracted to shared utility in future story.\n20\t\n21\t## Token Report — dev-story\n22\t- Total tool calls: 22\n23\t- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 7, Edit: 13, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n24\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~800 lines), `npm run test:unit` (~600 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines)\n25\t- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n26\t- Redundant operations: one file read twice (workflow-parser.test.ts)\n27\t\n28\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — code-review (2026-04-03T02:55)\n29\t\n30\t- **HIGH fixed:** ~75 lines duplicated validation/integrity/defaults between `parseWorkflow()` and `resolveWorkflow()`. Extracted `validateAndResolve()`.\n31\t- **HIGH fixed:** `loadWorkflowPatch` silently swallowed EACCES permission errors. Now throws on permission errors, null only for missing files.\n32\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Empty catch clause in embedded workflow loading discarded original error message.\n33\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** No test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'custom' })` path. Added.\n34\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `deepMerge` duplicated in agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts.\n35\t- **LOW (not fixed):** Custom workflow detection re-reads file that `parseWorkflow` also reads (minor I/O waste).\n36\t- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n37\t\n38\t## Token Report — code-review\n39\t- Total tool calls: 18\n40\t- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n41\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~20 lines)\n42\t- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n43\t- Redundant operations: none\n44\t\n45\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — verification (2026-04-03T02:58)\n46\t\n47\t- **Proof format mismatch:** First proof used `### AC N:` (h3) instead of `## AC N:` (h2) and lacked bash/output block pairs. Rewrote.\n48\t- **Warnings:** Showboat not installed, no exec-plan — non-blocking.\n49\t- **BATS integration tests:** All show exit code 127 (pre-existing, unrelated).\n50\t- **Branch coverage 79.12%:** Below 80% for branches specifically, but AC says \"80%+ coverage\" without specifying branches. Statement 93.96%, functions 100%.\n51\t- All 10/10 ACs passed with real evidence.\n52\t\n53\t## Token Report — verification\n54\t- Total tool calls: 16\n55\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n56\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test | tail -80` (~80 lines), `vitest run workflow-parser.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (~45 lines)\n57\t- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n58\t- Redundant operations: vitest coverage run twice, npm run test:unit run twice\n59\t\n60\t### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — create-story (2026-04-03T07:06)\n61\t\n62\t- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** The epic's ACs for story 9.2 are sparse (3 lines). Expanded to 10 ACs covering error paths, backward compatibility, edge cases (custom + patch coexistence), and agent resolution.\n63\t- **Story is smaller than expected:** Most heavy lifting done in story 9-1. resolveWorkflow() already accepts a `name` parameter and detects full custom workflows. This story is primarily CLI plumbing + test coverage.\n64\t- **Risk — user-level custom workflows unsupported:** resolveWorkflow() only checks project-level for full custom workflows. User-level custom workflows are only supported as patches, not full workflows.\n65\t\n66\t## Token Report — create-story\n67\t- Total tool calls: 17\n68\t- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 6, Edit: 0, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 5\n69\t- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads\n70\t- Redundant operations: Two separate Glob calls for same pattern — minor\n71\t\n72\t### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — dev-story (2026-04-03T07:10)\n73\t\n74\tNo issues reported. Clean implementation — existing resolveWorkflow() already supported the name parameter.\n75\t\n76\t## Token Report — dev-story\n77\t- Total tool calls: 12\n78\t- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Glob: 2\n79\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n80\t- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n81\t- Redundant operations: none\n82\t\n83\t### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — code-review (2026-04-03T07:15)\n84\t\n85\t- **HIGH fixed:** Path traversal vulnerability via `--workflow` CLI flag — no input sanitization allowed `../` sequences to escape `.codeharness/workflows/` directory. Fixed with regex validation.\n86\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Wrong error variable in `run.ts` fallback catch block (`err` → `fallbackErr`).\n87\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Test assertions strengthened for `cwd` and error message content.\n88\t- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicate test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'nonexistent' })` between 9.2 section and pre-existing test.\n89\t- **LOW (not fixed):** Legacy fallback path in run.ts should eventually be removed.\n90\t- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n91\t\n92\t## Token Report — code-review\n93\t- Total tool calls: 19\n94\t- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n95\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff` (~200 lines)\n96\t- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n97\t- Redundant operations: none\n98\t\n99\t### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — verification (2026-04-03T07:20)\n100\t\n101\t- **Proof format issues:** Initial proof had 8/10 ACs because ACs 9-10 lacked bash+output paired code blocks. Fixed.\n102\t- **Tier header mismatch:** Proof used `**Verification tier:**` instead of `**Tier:**` — validator regex only matches latter. Fixed.\n103\t- **Observation:** Vitest ANSI escape codes make grep-based extraction unreliable from raw output.\n104\t\n105\t## Token Report — verification\n106\t- Total tool calls: 20\n107\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 4, Grep: 8, Edit: 3, Write: 1\n108\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~600 lines ANSI), `npm run test:unit -- --coverage` (~100 lines)\n109\t- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n110\t- Redundant operations: Coverage and test:unit run separately (could be one), verify run 3 times due to proof format fixes\n111\t\n112\t### 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types — create-story (2026-04-03T06:20)\n113\t\n114\t- **Workaround: Epic numbering mismatch.** Sprint-status uses \"Epic 10\" (10-1, 10-2...) but epics file uses \"Epic 1\" internally (Story 1.1, 1.2...). Mapped 10-1 to Epic 1 Story 1.1 in the multi-framework epics.\n115\t- **Risk: `OutputContract` type placement.** Architecture places `output-contract.ts` as a separate module, but the type needs to be in `types.ts` because `DispatchOpts` references it. TYPE in `types.ts`, IMPLEMENTATION in later story.\n116\t- **Observation:** Existing `AgentDriver` interface is very different from target (process-based vs async-iterable-based). Deprecated type preservation important — 288 lines of tests against old interface.\n117\t\n118\t## Token Report — create-story\n119\t- Total tool calls: 16\n120\t- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n121\t- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n122\t- Redundant operations: none\n123\t\n124\t### 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types — dev-story (2026-04-03T06:25)\n125\t\n126\tNo issues reported. Clean implementation — 4 files modified, 30+ tests, all 4219 tests passing.\n127\t\n128\t## Token Report — dev-story\n129\t- Total tool calls: 22\n130\t- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 13, Grep: 3, Write: 3, Glob: 1\n131\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~40 lines), `npx tsc --noEmit` (~30 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines)\n132\t- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads\n133\t- Redundant operations: none significant\n134\t\n135\t### 10-1-agentdriver-interface-types — code-review (2026-04-03T06:30)\n136\t\n137\t- **HIGH fixed:** `DispatchOpts` fields mutable — drivers could mutate caller's options. Added `readonly`.\n138\t- **MEDIUM fixed (x4):** Mutable fields on `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus`.\n139\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Test name/count mismatch (\"8 event types\" vs 9 actual).\n140\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** `ErrorCategory` exhaustiveness test was cosmetic, not compile-time safe. Added `never` switch.\n141\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `ACStatus.status` is typed as `string` rather than a union type.\n142\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `SpawnOpts` deprecated type still uses mutable fields (scheduled for removal in 10-3).\n143\t- **Architecture concern:** Story AC #1 added `capabilities` to `AgentDriver` interface, which isn't in the architecture spec (Decision 1). Spec drift.\n144\t- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n145\t\n146\t## Token Report — code-review\n147\t- Total tool calls: 18\n148\t- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 8, Grep: 2, Glob: 1,